      "id": "eed81f11ce0863bb",
      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "eed81f11ce0863bb",
        "text": "# 5. Make it up as you go.\nKarl Weick talks about bricolage, a French word that does not translate well. A bricoleur is a person that can routinely make what they need from what is at hand. They can make a uniquely useful machine from spare parts in a barn and it may do the job better than anything on the market. Gather all the bricoleurs you can find for this kind of work.\n"
      },
      "date": 1648795145683
    },
    {
      "type": "edit",
      "id": "eed81f11ce0863bb",
      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "eed81f11ce0863bb",
        "text": "# 5. Make it up as you go.\nKarl Weick talks about bricolage, a French word that does not translate well. A bricoleur is a person that can routinely make what they need from what is at hand. They can make a uniquely useful machine from spare parts in a barn and it may do the job better than anything on the market. Gather all the bricoleurs you can find for this kind of work.\n\n>Bricolage--A form of improvisation practiced by some, using whatever resources and repertoire come to hand, in order to perform the immediate task. A person who practices bricolage is called a bricoleur.\n\nIn a paper called Organizational Redesign as Improvisation, Karl Weick identifies the following requirements for successful bricolage.\n- intimate knowledge of resources - careful observation and listening\n- trusting one's ideas\n- self-correcting structures, with feedback\n\nImprovisation is a related idea. Quite different than \"experimentation\". Think of the \"improvisational organization\" as a variant on the \"learning organization.\" More real time, more masterful. That is what is needed.\n\nFor an in depth understanding of this concept and also a related exploration of \"wisdom as improvisation \" see these articles by Karl Weick .\nThe Attitude of Wisdom: Ambivalence as the Optimal Compromise, Karl E. Weick.\n\n\n"
      },
      "date": 1648795164719
    },
